    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village’s name honors Samuel Willis, a 17th‑century settler, whose family homes stood there until the 1950s.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3,
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Williston_Park%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Williston Park’s public library, the Del Vecchio Memorial Library, sits in Village Hall and is part of the Nassau Library System.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10,
        11,
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Williston_Park%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The area evolved from Hempstead Plains farmland into a residential enclave as transportation improved and families moved east from New York City.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
